This paper deals with fairness in machine learning, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the impact of fairness criteria on the well-being of different groups over time, which could be relevant to the subfield of cybernetics (cs.CY). Additionally, the paper analyzes the potential harm caused by fairness criteria, which could be relevant to the subfield of cryptography (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the importance of measurement and temporal modeling in evaluating fairness criteria, which could be relevant to the subfield of social and information networks (cs.SI).
